modules.description: Provides a mechanism to control loop execution with explicit break and continue operations, allowing for structured exit from unbounded loops. Operates on custom loop states and exception handlers to manage flow. Enables clean termination of long-running processes or event loops based on internal conditions.

Provides functions to control infinite loops by breaking or skipping iterations. Operates with unit-returning functions to execute and manage loop behavior. Used to implement custom loop logic in scenarios requiring dynamic control over execution flow, such as event handling or polling.
